Subject: [PATCH 4/5] rotateinfo: Display either rotation lock or orientation
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

We listen for the shell's rotation-manager property first
and if that show up connect to `orientation-locked` to
update the icon status.

If no orientation manager is available use the current
portrait/landscape mode.

Add helpers that allow to switch between the two modes.

Signed-off-by: Guido Günther <guido.gunther@puri.sm>
---
 src/rotateinfo.c | 147 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++------
